<p>
<a class="emphasized">Tenacity</a> is an easy-to-use, cross-platform<br/>
multi-track audio editor/recorder<br/>
for Windows, MacOS, GNU/Linux and other operating systems<br/>
and is developed by a group of volunteers as open-source software.<br/>
</p>

<h2>Features</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">Recording</a> from audio devices (real or virtual)
  </li>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">Export & Import</a> a wide range of audio formats<br/>
    &#9;(extendible with FFmpeg)
  </li>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">High Quality</a>
    including up to 32-bit float audio support
  </li>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">Plug-Ins</a> providing support for
    VST, LV2, and AU plugins
  </li>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">Scripting</a>
   in the built-in scripting language Nyquist,<br/>
   or in Python, Perl and other languages with named pipes
  </li>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">Editing</a> arbitrary sampling and multi-track timeline
  </li>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">Accessibility</a> including editing via keyboard,<br/>
    screen reader support and narration support
  </li>
  <li>
    <a class="emphasized">Tools</a>
    useful in the analysis of signals, including audio
  </li>
</ul>

